{"title_page": "Latin Grammy Award for Best Samba/Pagode Album", "text_new": "{{Infobox award\n| name = Latin Grammy Award for Best Samba/Pagode Album\n| description = Vocal or instrumental Samba/Pagode albums containing at least 51% playing time of newly recorded material.  For Solo artists, duos or groups.\n| image    = \n| presenter = [[The Latin Recording Academy]]\n| country = United States\n| year = 2000\n| holder         = [[Alexandre Pires]] for ''Eletrosamba - Ao Vivo''\n| website = [http://www.latingrammy.com/ latingrammy.com]\n}}\n\nThe '''Latin Grammy Award for Best Samba/Pagode Album''' is an honor presented annually at the [[Latin Grammy Award]]s, a ceremony that recognizes excellence and creates a wider awareness of cultural diversity and contributions of Latin recording artists in the United States and internationally. According to the category description guide for the [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2012|13th Latin Grammy Awards]], the award is for vocal or instrumental Samba/Pagode albums containing at least 51% playing time of newly recorded material.  For Solo artists, duos or groups.\n\n==2010s==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Winner !! Nominees\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2014|2014]]\n|\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Alcione Nazareth|Alcione]] \u2014 ''Eterna Alegria Ao Vivo''\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] \u2014 ''Enredo''\n*[[Paula Lima]] \u2014 ''O Samba \u00c9 Do Bem''\n*[[Diogo Nogueira]] \u2014 ''Mais Amor''\n*[[Maria Rita]] \u2014 ''Cora\u00e7\u00e3o A Batucar''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2013|2013]]\n|[[Alexandre Pires]] \u2014 ''Eletrosamba - Ao Vivo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Diogo Nogueira]] \u2014 ''Ao Vivo Em Cuba''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] \u2014 ''Vida Que Segue''\n*Various Artists \u2014 ''Sambabook Martinho da Vila 2''\n*Dora Vergueiro \u2014 ''Dora Vergueiro''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2012|2012]]\n|[[Beth Carvalho]] \u2014 ''Nosso Samba T\u00e1 Na Rua''<BR/>\nEmilio Santiago \u2014 ''So Dan\u00e7o Samba Ao Vivo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*Alcione \u2014 ''Duas Faces Ao Vivo Na Mangueira''\n*Sorriso Maroto \u2014 ''15 Anos Ao Vivo''\n*Thiaguinho \u2014 ''Ousadia & Alegria''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2011|2011]]\n|[[Exaltasamba]] for ''Exaltasamba 25 Anos - Ao Vivo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] \u2014 ''Filosofia de Vida''\n*[[Fundo de Quintal]] \u2014 ''Nossa Verdade''\n*[[Diogo Nogueira]] \u2014 ''Sou Eu - Ao Vivo''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] \u2014 ''Vida da Minha Vida''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2010|2010]]\n|[[Diogo Nogueira]] for ''T\u00f4 Fazendo a Minha Parte''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Alcione Nazareth|Alcione]] for ''Acesa''\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Poeta da Cidade: Martinho Canta Noel''\n*Grupo Revela\u00e7\u00e3o for ''Ao Vivo no Morro''\n*[[Monobloco]] for ''Monobloco 10''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''MTV Especial Zeca Pagodinho Uma Prova de Amor ao Vivo''}}\n|}\n\n==2000s==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Winner !! Nominees\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2009|2009]]\n|[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''O Pequeno Burgu\u00eas!!''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Arlindo Cruz]] for ''MTV Ao Vivo''\n*[[Exaltasamba]] for ''Ao Vivo Na Ilha Da Magia''\n*Harmonia Do Samba for ''Rom\u00e2ntico Ao Vivo''\n*Inimigos Da Hp for ''Ao Vivo Em Zoodstock''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Uma Prova De Amor''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2008|2008]]\n|[[Paulinho da Viola]] for ''Ac\u00fastico MTV'' & [[Maria Rita]] for ''Samba Meu''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Beth Carvalho]] for ''Canta O Samba Da Bahia Ao Vivo''\n*[[Arlindo Cruz]] for ''Sambista Perfeito''\n*[[Luiz Melodia]] for ''Esta\u00e7\u00e3o Melodia''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2007|2007]]\n|[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Ac\u00fastico MTV 2 Gafieira''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Jorge Arag\u00e3o]] for ''E A\u00ed?''\n*[[Beth Carvalho]] for ''40 Anos de Carreira: Ao Vivo No Teatro Municipal Vol. 2''\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Do Brasil e do Mundo''\n*[[Mart'n\u00e1lia]] for ''Mart'n\u00e1lia Em Berlim Ao Vivo''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2006|2006]]\n|[[Marisa Monte]] for ''Universo Ao Meu Redor''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Alcione Nazareth|Alcione]] for ''Uma Nova Paix\u00e3o Ao Vivo''\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Brasilatinidade Ao Vivo''\n*[[Dem\u00f4nios da Garoa]] for ''Ao Vivo''\n*[[Jair Rodrigues]] for ''Alma Negra''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2005|2005]]\n|[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Brasilatinidade''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Jorge Arag\u00e3o]] for ''Ao Vivo 3''\n*[[Beth Carvalho]] for ''A Madrinha Do Samba / Ao Vivo Convida''\n*[[Wilson das Neves]] for ''Bras\u00e3o de Orfeu''\n*[[Nei Lopes]] for ''Partido Ao Cubo''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''\u00c0 Vera''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2004|2004]]\n|Nana, Dori and Danilo for ''Para Caymmi. de Nana, Dori e Danilo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Jorge Arag\u00e3o]] for ''Da Noite Pro Dia''\n*Monarco for ''Uma Historia Do Samba''\n*[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Ac\u00fastico MTV''\n*Velha Guarda Do Salgueiro for ''Velha Guarda Do Salgueiro''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2003|2003]]\n|[[Alcione Nazar\u00e9|Alcione]] for ''Ao Vivo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*Leandro Braga for ''Primeira Dama - A M\u00fasica De Dona Ivone Lara''\n*[[Teresa Cristina (singer)|Teresa Cristina]] and Grupo Semente for ''A M\u00fasica De Paulinho Da Viola''\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Voz e Cora\u00e7\u00e3o''\n*[[Jair Rodrigues]] for ''Int\u00e9rprete''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2002|2002]]\n|[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Deixa A Vida Me Levar''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Martinho da Vila]] for ''Da Roca e Da Cidade''\n*Claudio Jorge for ''Coisa De Chefe''\n*Riachao for ''Humanenochum''\n*Nelson Sargento for ''Flores Em Vida''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2001|2001]]\n|[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Agua Da Minha Sede''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Beth Carvalho]] for ''Pagode De Mesa 2 - Ao Vivo''\n*Harmonia do Samba for ''O Rodo''\n*[[Jair Rodrigues]] for ''500 Anos De Folia - Volume 2''\n*Various Artists for ''Casa de Samba 4''}}\n|-\n|[[Latin Grammy Awards of 2000|2000]]\n|[[Zeca Pagodinho]] for ''Zeca Pagodinho ao Vivo''\n|{{smalldiv|\n*[[Alcione Nazare